<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53093a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53093a">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53093a"> 93(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ron (spear) / Priwen (shield)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Arthur himself, carrying &ldquo;on his shoulder <mark>the shield Priwen</mark>,&rdquo; and armed with <mark>Ron, his spear</mark>, and; &ldquo;Caliburn, best of swords, that was forged within the Isle of Avalon,&rdquo; performed prodigies of valour in that battle. <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA3"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 76</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Ron was the name given to King Arthur&apos;s spear that was wrought with magic by Griffin of Kaermerddin. Priwen was his shield, a stout one fashioned of ivory and gold. </mm> </dd></dl>
